{% extends 'base.jinja2' %}

{% block title %}FAQ - {% endblock %}

{% block page_header %}Frequently Asked Questions{% endblock %}

{% macro question(q='') %}
  <div class="item">
    <div class="content">
      <div class="header">Q: {{ q }}</div>
      <div class="description">
        {{ caller() }}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
{% endmacro %}

{% block content %}

  <div class="ui items">
    {% call question(q='What does "EOJ" stand for?') %}
      <p>A: EOJ is the abbreviation for ECNU Online Judge.</p>
    {% endcall %}
    {% call question(q='Which languages have you supported?') %}
      <p>A: We have already supported C, C++, Java, Python(3).</p>
    {% endcall %}

    {% call question(q="What does a typical solution look like?") %}
      <p>A: Here is an A + B Solution for each language:</p>
      <p>For language C:</p>
      <pre><code>#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;
int main()
{
    int a, b;
    scanf("%d%d", &a, &b);
    printf("%d\n", a + b);
}</code></pre>
      <p>For language C++:</p>
      <pre><code>#include &lt;iostream&gt;
using namespace std;
int main()
{
    int a, b;
    cin >> a >> b;
    cout << a + b << endl;
    return 0;
}</code></pre>
      <p>For language Java:</p>
      <pre><code>import java.util.*;
public class Main {
    public static void main(String args[]) {
        Scanner cin = new Scanner(System.in);
        int a, b;
        a = cin.nextInt();
        b = cin.nextInt();
        System.out.println(a + b);
    }
}</code></pre>
      <p>For Python:</p>
      <pre><code>a, b = map(int, input().split())
print(a + b)</code></pre>
    {% endcall %}

    {% call question(q="Is there a way to tell whether the environment is on Online Judge or not?") %}
      <p>A: For C/C++, macro ONLINE_JUDGE is predefined in the program. For Java and Python, currently, no.</p>
    {% endcall %}

    {% call question(q="Should I use %lld or %I64d?") %}
      <p>A: We are under Linux environment. So definitely %lld.</p>
    {% endcall %}

    {% call question(q="Is there any another difference on judge strategy between languages?") %}
      <p>A: Java has a -150ms bonus on the time record for each test case. Memory display in Java is currently not
        available (always 0 sadly), but you can still get an error if you ask for too much memory.</p>
    {% endcall %}

    {% call question(q="Why is my memory status ridiculously high / low?") %}
      <p>A: Unfortunately there are no known solution to the memory problem. We are able to get a MLE correctly, but not a memory
      status. When it comes to Java, this problem gets worse. That's why all memory statuses for Java are 0KB.</p>
    {% endcall %}

    {% call question(q="What is the length limit of our code?") %}
      <p>A: Code should contain no more than 65536 characters.</p>
    {% endcall %}

    {% call question(q="What is the version of compiler on the server?") %}
      <p>A: We have Ubuntu 14.04 on the server, with Java version 1.7.0_121, g++ 4.8.4 and Python 3.4.3. Python 2 is
      currently not supported on the server.</p>
    {% endcall %}

    {% call question(q="What are the compile commands?") %}
      <p>A: Below are the compile commands for C, C++, Java, Python.</p>
      <div class="ui list">
        <div class="item">C: <pre>gcc -DONLINE_JUDGE -O2 -w -std=c99 main.c -lm -o main</pre></div>
        <div class="item">C++: <pre>g++ -DONLINE_JUDGE -O2 -w -fmax-errors=3 -std=c++11 main.cpp -lm -o main</pre></div>
        <div class="item">Java: <pre>javac Main.java -encoding UTF8</pre></div>
        <div class="item">Python: <pre>python3 -m py_compile solution.py</pre></div>
      </div>
    {% endcall %}

    {% call question(q="Why did my solution disappear from online status?") %}
      <p>A: Normally it is because the problem is hidden, or you have submitted it in a contest.</p>
    {% endcall %}

    {% call question(q="Can I delete my blog?") %}
      <p>A: Currently you can't. You can hide it though. Still, be careful when you create a blog.</p>
    {% endcall %}

  </div>


{% endblock %}
